FBIS3-5405 "dreas045_c_94011" FBIS-EAS-94-045 Document Type:Daily Report 8 Mar 1994 North Korea Hanchongnyon Claims Campus Surveillance in Seoul SK0703105894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1010 GMT 7 Mar 94 SK0703105894 Pyongyang KCNA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Pyongyang, March 7 (KCNA) -- The South Korean Federation of General Student Councils (Hanchongnyon) called a press conference at Hanyang University in Seoul on Friday and released a statement on the fact that a police officer belonging to the puppet Seoul District Police Agency had sneaked into the university and was nabbed while watching the tendencies of university students, according to radio report from Seoul. The statement charges that the police had been engaged in campus surveillance after forming an exclusive detective group in charge of Hanchongnyon five months ago. "This campus surveillance is designed to prevent a struggle of students against rice market opening," noted the statement.
